    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Jim to Mr. Paul A. Rockwell <date value="1916-09-12">September 12th ‘16</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-09-12">September 12th ‘16</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Paul:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
        		<p>
            Some class to the
            paper, eh [sic] what?  Got
            your interesting long letter
            this A. M.  Its great about
            Kiffin.  Heard the news from
            the Capt. last night.  He
            said the snow bird got one 
            too and that Skip was
            en farme [sic] in the Verdun
            marshes.
            </p><p>
            I am going to try
            a new elixer  [sic] to morrow and
            
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            And [sic] see what it does.  I
            know I’ll be laid out for
            24 hrs., for one thing.
            </p><p>
            2,000 motor lorries breezed
            thru [sic] here to day en route for
            Somme to move troops to the 
            Champagne offensive.  Christ I’d
            like to see that but if
            its pulled off soon am
            afraid I’ll miss it.
            </p><p>
            The Cotter person whom
            I tried to rape is loading 
            me down with magazines
            and letters.  Try it Paul.
            It wins you a home.
            </p><p>
            
            <pb n="[p.3]"/>
            
            Maybe Coleman or Mc <unclear>Kiuem [sp?]</unclear>
            might do.  Hope those pictures
            are running when I get
            in.  The Doc seems discouraging
            and it may be ten days
            before they turn me loose.
            </p><p>
            Sorry you have had so
            much trouble about the
            cable.  I wouldn’t have
            bothered you had I known.
            </p><p>
            That uniform I had made
            must be lost.  It has
            never even shown up at 
            Bar le Duc.
            </p><p>
            	
            <pb n="[p.4]"/>
            
            Did you get the letter for
            Pechkoff  I sent you just
            before coming here?  Hope the 
            lad has great success in
            the God damned States.
            </p><p>
            Drop me the news when
            you get time and let me 
            know as soon as possible
            how old Grundy makes out
            with Munsey.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>Your ally [sic]</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            Hopital Mixte<lb/>
            Vitry-le-Francois<lb/>
            Marne.
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
